  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;for the implementation of a civil society assessment of student learning in East Africa&quot;</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&quot;This grant to Hivos would provide continued support to Uwezo, a nationwide, citizen-led assessment of student learning in Kenya, Tanzania, and Uganda. Uwezo is the largest annual assessment of children&#x2019;s learning in Africa; in 2012 alone Uwezo tested nearly 350,000 children in about 11,000 communities. The results have sparked national, regional, and global debates about the magnitude of the learning crisis for schoolchildren. This renewal grant would support the ongoing efforts to collect, analyze, and communicate the results of the nationwide learning assessment to stimulate citizen action and oversight in education and policy reform.&quot;</narrative>
  </description>
